title: Local dog who refused to leave trapped friend honored by governor
text:
A Vashon Island dog who refused to leave her friend was honored by Gov. Jay Inslee Thursday.
Tillie stood guard by her friend, Phoebe, after she became stuck in a cistern last month.
Tillie and Phoebe were reported missing by their owners, and Vashon Island Pet Protectors posted the dogs’ photos over social media.
For nearly a week, Tillie, a Setter mix, stayed by Phoebe’s side, with the exception of the few minutes each day she went for help.
Volunteers helped search for the missing Setter mix and Basset Hound and investigated when a community member called saying they had seen a “reddish” dog on their property for the past few days.
When searchers called her name, Tillie responded with a bark. She then led them to where Phoebe was stuck, perched atop concrete rubble that held her out of the water of the cistern.
Inslee will presented Tillie with the Washingtonian of the Day award for her bravery and loyalty.
